item.title: Democrats file police complaints over Trump’s posts accusing them of sedition- two received bomb threats.
item.description:
“SEDITIOUS BEHAVIOR, punishable by DEATH!” Trump wrote in a separate post. One of 6 Democrats, Mark Kelly, treated TRUMPS death threat as gravely serious. Mark Edward Kelly (born February 21, 1964) is an American politician, retired astronaut, and former naval officer serving as the senior United States senator from Arizona, a seat he has held since 2020. He is a member of the Democratic Party.
During his Navy career, Kelly received two Defense Superior Service Medals; one Legion of Merit; two Distinguished Flying Crosses; four Air Medals (two individual/two strike flight) with Combat "V"; two Navy Commendation Medals, (one with combat "V"); one Navy Achievement Medal; two Southwest Asia Service Medals; one Navy Expeditionary Medal; two Sea Service Deployment Ribbons; a NASA Distinguished Service Medal; and an Overseas Service Ribbon.
Kelly's first trip into space was as pilot of STS-108. After several delays, Endeavour lifted off on December 5, 2001, on the final Shuttle mission of 2001. In July 2006, Kelly piloted STS-121 Discovery, the second "Return to Flight" mission after the loss of Columbia in February 2003. Because of weather delays, STS-121 became the first shuttle mission to launch on the Fourth of July.
On June 21, 2011, Kelly announced that he would leave NASA's astronaut corps and the U.S. Navy effective October 1. He announced his retirement on his Facebook page, writing: "Words cannot convey my deep gratitude for the opportunities I have been given to serve our great nation. From the day I entered the United States Merchant Marine Academy in the summer of 1982 to the moment I landed the Space Shuttle Endeavour three weeks ago, it has been my privilege to advance the ideals that define the United States of America." A true patriot, TRUMP isn't.

item.title: Holy Rave!
item.description: A Catholic priest turned DJ just threw a rave outside a 14th-century cathedral on behalf of the Pope. To celebrate Archbishop Bernard Bober’s 75th birthday in Slovakia, the Vatican enlisted Padre Guilherme, a priest who’s also a professional electronic music producer to lead an unforgettable celebration. Under the Pope’s blessing, the event featured lasers, projection mapping, pulsing bass, and a full crowd, all outside St. Elisabeth Cathedral.

item.title: Cat interference pattern
item.description:
Do not interfere the cat Yes I'm aware this is not an actually an interference pattern. So for the pun resistant pendant in us all, here are some actual interference patterns.
Interference patterns are the result of two or more coherent waves overlapping, causing periodic regions of constructive interference (reinforcement) and destructive interference (cancellation).
These first two examples are in water, but interference patterns can occur in any form of coherent waves including sound and light
Active noise cancellation headphones also do their magic by using interference patterns
An explanation on noise cancelling from Hannah Fry on the BBC YouTube channel: https://youtu.be/DcdRlq4_-yw Wiki: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Noise-cancelling_headphones

item.title: GovBrief Today #295
item.description: "MTG turns on Trump and resigns. Mamdani and Trump are new best friends. I am so confused." Political scientist Larry Sabato, the academic who calls elections before the networks, wrote that on X tonight. Marjorie Taylor Greene is disappearing into a chaotic haze of insults she's been trading with Trump over the Epstein files. Trump called NYC Mayor-Elect Mamdani a communist yesterday and wouldn't stop praising him today after an Oval Office meeting. Meanwhile, nurses are learning that their student loans don't qualify as a professional's do, but chiropractors and theologians made the cut. The big White House secret is that there is no grand plan. Trump famously doesn't attend briefings or read much. He runs the presidency like a hot dog stand in his native New York, reacting to the flow around him, and knocking off early when the mood strikes. Sabato's been doing this for decades. He's never confused. Today he's confused. Finding the patterns in the chaos and meticulously documenting it all is why GovBrief Today started and why we continue every day.
